00:33:03,650 --> 00:33:06,140
对，我真的感觉好多了
Yeah, you know, I feel really well.

318
00:33:06,140 --> 00:33:09,640
我是说，就好像没有发生过事情一样，这太不可思议了
I mean, it's almost as if nothing had happened. It's incredible.

319
00:33:09,640 --> 00:33:13,150
- 这都要感谢维迪葛斯教授  - 维迪葛斯？
- And all thanks to professor Verdegast.  - Verdegast?

320
00:33:13,150 --> 00:33:15,140
- 他来看你？ - 对
- He came to look at you?  - Yeah.

321
00:33:15,140 --> 00:33:17,640
请进
Come in.

322
00:33:20,140 --> 00:33:22,140
嗨，帕罗斯
Hi, Pavlos.

323
00:33:33,060 --> 00:33:35,050
谢谢你
Thank you.

324
00:33:37,060 --> 00:33:40,060
你最好留意那个打火机，他很喜欢它
You'd better keep an eye on that lighter. He really likes it.

325
00:33:40,060 --> 00:33:42,050
好的，不过我不觉得他是小偷
Yes, but I don't think he's a thief.

326
00:33:42,060 --> 00:33:44,050
至少你知道
At least you know.

327
00:33:44,050 --> 00:33:48,060
- 你要在这里吃饭吗？ - 对，她们限制我的饮食
- Are you eating up here?  - Yeah, they put me on a restricted diet.

328
00:33:48,060 --> 00:33:51,060
限制饮食还有酒？
And on a restricted diet, they give you wine?

329
00:33:51,060 --> 00:33:55,050
这是维迪葛斯教授的主意，他说这可以帮助我的血液
That's professor Verdegast's idea. Says it'll build up my blood.

330
00:34:01,390 --> 00:34:04,390
铃声，天啊，这表示在吃晚餐之前只剩下十五分钟
The bell. Oh, god. That means it's only 15 minutes till supper.

331
00:34:04,390 --> 00:34:06,890
我最好去换衣服
I'd better change.

332
00:34:06,890 --> 00:34:09,890
- 待会见  - 好的
- Ciao. See you later.  - Okay.

333
00:35:40,380 --> 00:35:42,380
在哪里？在哪里？
Where? Where?

334
00:35:42,380 --> 00:35:44,390
到处都有，整层楼
Everywhere. The whole floor.

335
00:35:44,890 --> 00:35:47,390
真恶心！真让人恶心！
It's disgusting! It's disgusting!

336
00:35:47,390 --> 00:35:49,880
- 它们从哪里来的？ - 我不知道！我们去看看吧！
- Where are they coming from?  - I don't know! Let's go and see!

337
00:35:49,880 --> 00:35:53,390
- 它们从天花板来的  - 在还没解决之前，所有人都下楼
- They're coming from the ceiling.  - In the meantime, everybody downstairs.

338
00:36:06,560 --> 00:36:08,550
不要让任何人上来
Don't let anyone come up.

339
00:37:04,050 --> 00:37:08,050
我很抱歉，真是羞愧，请原谅我
I'm sorry. Truly mortified. Please excuse me.

340
00:37:08,050 --> 00:37:10,050
不过这跟你并没有关系，夫人
But it was nothing to do with you, madame.

341
00:37:10,050 --> 00:37:13,050
当然没有，女孩们，这不是布兰克夫人的错
No, of course not, girls. It was not madame Blanc's fault.

342
00:37:13,050 --> 00:37:15,790
我们透过邮件
We ordered those cases of food by mail...

343
00:37:16,300 --> 00:37:18,300
向我们认为诚实可靠的公司订购食物
From a reliable firm that we thought to be honest.

344
00:37:18,710 --> 00:37:20,220
很显然，它们运到时已经腐烂了
Obviously, It arrived spoiled.

345
00:37:20,720 --> 00:37:22,720
几天之内，就发生了这些事
In a few days' time, you see what happened.

346
00:37:22,720 --> 00:37:25,460
- 喔，这真是可怕  - 对啊，有一只还掉进我的嘴巴
- Oh, it was awful.  - Yes, one got in my mouth.

347
00:37:25,460 --> 00:37:29,470
我想我们还是幸运的，那些虫子只到了顶楼的下一层
I suppose we're fortunate those things only reached the floor below the attic.

348
00:37:29,470 --> 00:37:32,470
- 那其他楼层没有问题吗？ - 对，我们检查过了
- Are the other floors all right?  - Yes. We checked them out.

349
00:37:32,470 --> 00:37:34,460
只有学生寝室的楼层
Just the floor where the students' rooms are.

350
00:37:34,460 --> 00:37:37,460
好吧，我早上会处理消毒的问题
Well, I'll take care of the problem of fumigating in the morning.

351
00:37:37,460 --> 00:37:40,970
问题还没解决之前，今晚我先做一个临时的安排
In the meantime, for tonight, I've thought of a makeshift arrangement.

352
00:37:40,970 --> 00:37:43,460
亲爱的，你可以去看看他们进展如何吗？
Go and see how they're getting along, will you, dear?

353
00:37:44,960 --> 00:37:47,460
男孩们都很体贴的提供协助
The boys have kindly offered to help,

354
00:37:47,460 --> 00:37:49,970
他们和仆人们把练习厅布置成一个大寝室
And they and the servants are turning the practice hall into a dormitory.

355
00:37:50,470 --> 00:37:53,960
如果你们有人选择要外出住宿，我没有任何反对
If some of you choose to find hotel rooms, I'll have no objections.

356
00:37:53,960 --> 00:37:55,960
但是现在已经很晚了，无论如何…
But it's already late, and in any case,

357
00:37:55,960 --> 00:37:57,960
这种不便只有一个晚上而已
The inconvenience will only be for one night.

358
00:37:57,960 --> 00:38:00,300
我们全部都一起睡
We'll all sleep together.

359
00:38:01,800 --> 00:38:03,790
好极了！你还好吗？
Bravo. You all right?

360
00:38:03,790 --> 00:38:06,300
- 是的，谢谢你  - 很好
- Yes, thank you.  - Fine.

361
00:38:06,800 --> 00:38:08,800
- 一切都还好吗？ - 是的，谢谢你
- Is everything all right?  - Yes, thank you.

362
00:38:09,300 --> 00:38:10,800
- 很好  - 你还好吗？
- Good.  - Are you all right?

363
00:38:11,300 --> 00:38:12,790
是的，布兰克夫人，谢谢你
Yes, madame Blanc. Thank you.

364
00:38:13,290 --> 00:38:15,790
- 喔，这样很舒服，就像露营一样  - 很好
- Oh, it's very comfortable. Just like being in camp.  - Good.

365
00:38:16,300 --> 00:38:18,300
你也要跟我们一起睡在这里吗，布兰克夫人？
Are you sleeping here with us, too, Madame Blanc?

366
00:38:18,800 --> 00:38:20,790
当然，就跟坦娜小姐和其他老师一样
Certainly, as are all the other teachers and miss Tanner.

367
00:38:21,300 --> 00:38:23,790
其他老师也住在学校吗？
Do the teachers live here at school?

368
00:38:23,790 --> 00:38:25,790
没有，他们住在城里
No, they live in town.

369
00:38:25,790 --> 00:38:29,300
她们都在晚餐后九点半离开，就像钟表一样
They leave after supper at 9:30, just like clockwork.

370
00:38:29,470 --> 00:38:31,460
现在很晚了，我关掉电灯，你们不会害怕吧？
It's very late. You won't be afraid if I turn out the lights?

371
00:38:31,960 --> 00:38:34,460
- 各位晚安  - 晚安
- Good night, everyone.  - Good night. Good night.

372
00:39:13,630 --> 00:39:16,130
那家伙喜欢你吗？
Is that guy hot for you?

373
00:39:16,130 --> 00:39:18,090
- 也许  - 这真有趣
- Maybe.  - That's funny.

374
00:39:18,710 --> 00:39:21,000
我听过他是…嗯…
I heard he was, uh...

375
00:39:21,000 --> 00:39:26,550
- 当然，我不太喜欢说别人闲话  - 那是个好习惯
- Of course, I'm not much of a gossip.  - That's a good one.

376
00:39:27,130 --> 00:39:29,120
算了吧，你想追他却没有成功
Come on. You tried to get him and didn't make it.

377
00:39:29,120 --> 00:39:31,080
- 你说谎！那不是…  - 为什么你们两个不闭嘴？
- You liar! That's not...  - Why don't you two shut up?

378
00:39:31,080 --> 00:39:33,630
我们有些人想要睡觉
Some of us want to go to sleep.

379
00:39:38,620 --> 00:39:42,120
嘿，莎拉，忘了它吧，这没关系
Hey, Sara. Forget it. It's okay.

380
00:41:03,290 --> 00:41:05,450
苏西，你睡着了吗？
Suzy, are you asleep?

381
00:41:05,620 --> 00:41:08,200
- 你睡着了吗？ - 还没，有什么事吗？
- Were you sleeping?  - No. What's the matter?

382
00:41:10,210 --> 00:41:12,330
你听到那鼾声吗？
You hear that snoring?

383
00:41:12,330 --> 00:41:15,200
听起来怪怪的
It's weird.

384
00:41:15,200 --> 00:41:18,080
听到了吗？
Hear it?

385
00:41:18,080 --> 00:41:20,460
你想这声音是从哪里传来的？
Where do you think it's coming from?

386
00:41:26,790 --> 00:41:30,120
在帘子后面
Behind the sheet.

387
00:41:30,120 --> 00:41:32,630
说谎！
Lies!

388
00:41:32,630 --> 00:41:34,700
什么？
What?

389
00:41:38,200 --> 00:41:40,210
她们对我们说谎
They lied to us.

390
00:41:40,210 --> 00:41:42,710
校长在这里
The directress is here.

391
00:41:42,710 --> 00:41:46,200
那个打鼾的人是她
That's her, the one who's snoring.

392
00:41:46,200 --> 00:41:48,700
她是校长
She's the directress.

393
00:41:48,700 --> 00:41:51,170
- 你怎么知道？ - 我确定是她
- How do you know?  - I'm sure it's her.

394
00:41:54,450 --> 00:41:56,490
去年的一段时间
Last year, for a while,

395
00:41:56,490 --> 00:41:58,620
我住在客房的其中一间
I lived in one of the guest rooms...

396
00:41:58,620 --> 00:42:00,790
在顶楼的下面
Under the top of the stairs.

397
00:42:04,280 --> 00:42:06,290
有一天晚上
One night,

398
00:42:06,290 --> 00:42:10,040
我听到有人很晚进来
I heard someone coming very late in,

399
00:42:10,040 --> 00:42:13,200
躺到我隔壁房间的床上
Getting into bed in the room next to mine.

400
00:42:14,280 --> 00:42:16,370
然后…
And then...

401
00:42:16,370 --> 00:42:19,960
然后我听到这种古怪的打鼾声
Then I heard this weird kind of snoring.

402
00:42:19,960 --> 00:42:23,530
我告诉你，那真的很古怪，我永远都无法忘记
I tell you, it was so weird I never forgot it.

403
00:42:26,120 --> 00:42:28,540
注意听
Listen.

404
00:42:29,040 --> 00:42:31,110
你听到那声音了吗？
You hear that whistle?

405
00:42:32,320 --> 00:42:35,280
确实一模一样
It's exactly the same.

406
00:42:35,700 --> 00:42:39,290
隔天早上，布兰克夫人跟我说…
The next morning, madame Blanc told me...

407
00:42:39,290 --> 00:42:41,780
校长在学校忙到很晚…
That the directress had spent a few hours at the school...

408
00:42:41,780 --> 00:42:44,780
然后睡在我隔壁房里
And had slept in the room next to mine.

409
00:42:47,410 --> 00:42:48,950
你明白吗？
You see?

410
00:42:49,460 --> 00:42:53,030
所以我知道她是校长
So I know she's the directress.

411
00:42:53,030 --> 00:42:55,030
她在这里
She's here.

412
00:42:58,200 --> 00:43:00,200
她在那里
She's there.

413
00:43:00,210 --> 00:43:03,280
就在帘子后面
Right behind that sheet.

414
00:43:25,530 --> 00:43:28,530
我很感激你们能这么快的消毒好
Thank you. I'm grateful you can take care of the fumigating so promptly.

415
00:43:28,540 --> 00:43:31,530
- 早安，布兰克夫人  - 早安，丹尼尔
- Good morning, madame Blanc.  - Good morning, Daniel.

416
00:43:32,030 --> 00:43:35,030
- 现在一切都就序了吗？ - 都清理好了，夫人
- Is everything in order now?  - All cleaned up, madame.

417
00:43:35,030 --> 00:43:37,540
为了确定，我们还检查了其他楼层
Just to be sure, we checked the other floors too.

418
00:43:41,030 --> 00:43:43,530
坦娜小姐，抱歉
Miss Tanner. Excuse me.

419
00:43:43,530 --> 00:43:45,530
校长昨晚有睡在这里吗？
Did the directress sleep here last night?

420
00:43:45,530 --> 00:43:48,530
- 她没有，早安，丹尼尔  - 早安
- No, she didn't. Good morning, Daniel.  - Good morning.

421
00:43:49,030 --> 00:43:53,030
你知道她正在外面旅行，也许两个星期后她会回来看我们
You know she's away on a trip. Maybe she'll pay us a visit two weeks from now.

422
00:43:53,030 --> 00:43:56,540
抱歉，坦娜小姐，我今天早上要上什么课？
Excuse me, miss Tanner, But which class do I attend this morning?

423
00:43:56,540 --> 00:43:58,530
在红色房间的二年级班
The second-year class in the red room.

424
00:43:58,530 --> 00:44:00,530
谢谢你
Thank you.

425
00:44:59,280 --> 00:45:01,780
停止！
Stop!

426
00:45:01,780 --> 00:45:04,770
停止！停止！
Stop! Stop!

427
00:45:04,780 --> 00:45:07,780
够了！已经够了！
Enough. Enough!

428
00:45:07,780 --> 00:45:10,780
- 你知道发生什么事吗？你知道吗？ - 今天是什么日子？
- Do you know what happened? Do you know?  - What day is it?

429
00:45:10,780 --> 00:45:14,280
你那只满是跳蚤、恶心的狗，竟敢咬艾伯特！
Your lousy, disgusting dog has bitten Albert!

430
00:45:14,280 --> 00:45:16,280
它咬掉了一片艾伯特手臂上的肉
He took a piece out of Albert's arm.

431
00:45:16,780 --> 00:45:19,280
- 什么？ - 你们都听到了吗？
- What?  - Did you all hear that?

432
00:45:19,280 --> 00:45:22,280
那只卑鄙的狗想要让孩子残废
That miserable dog tried to mutilate a child.

433
00:45:22,280 --> 00:45:26,280
布兰克夫人必须紧急送艾伯特到第一诊疗中心缝伤口！
Madame Blanc had to rush Albert to a first-aid center to have stitches put in!

434
00:45:26,280 --> 00:45:29,780
- 那是不可能的  - 那我们一起去第一诊疗中心
- That's impossible.  - Let's go to the first-aid center.

435
00:45:30,280 --> 00:45:33,280
就算你看不到血，至少也能听到那个可怜孩子的哭声吧！
Even if you can't see the blood, at least you can hear the poor child's crying.

436
00:45:33,280 --> 00:45:35,270
够了！
That's enough now!

437
00:45:35,780 --> 00:45:39,280
我的狗很忠诚又乖巧，它从来没有伤害过任何人
My dog's a peaceful, faithful animal. He's never hurt anyone.

438
00:45:39,280 --> 00:45:41,780
那个孩子一定有先招惹它！
The boy must have done something to him first!

439
00:45:41,780 --> 00:45:45,270
喔，那可怜的小东西！可怜的小狗！
Oh, the poor little animal! The poor little puppy!

440
00:45:45,270 --> 00:45:49,780
假如我再看到它接近这个学校，我就要它死！
If I ever see him within a mile of this school again, I'll have him put to death!

441
00:45:49,780 --> 00:45:51,780
住口！
Stop it!

442
00:45:51,780 --> 00:45:53,770
我不允许你这样说，你听清楚了吗？
I won't allow such talk, you understand?

443
00:45:53,770 --> 00:45:56,780
你不允许吗？
You won't allow it?

444
00:45:56,780 --> 00:45:59,280
那么你和你的狗滚出去！
Then get out! You and your dog!

445
00:45:59,780 --> 00:46:02,770
- 走吧！ - 你这个婊子！
- Get moving!  - You bitch!

446
00:46:02,780 --> 00:46:04,770
出去！
Out!

447
00:46:04,770 --> 00:46:07,780
我正要出去，我正要出去
I'm going. I'm going.

448
00:46:07,780 --> 00:46:10,280
不过你要明白…
But try to understand that...

449
00:46:10,780 --> 00:46:14,270
我是瞎子，不是聋子
That I'm blind, not deaf.

450
00:46:14,770 --> 00:46:16,780
你明白吗？
Get it? Huh?

451
00:46:16,780 --> 00:46:18,780
不是聋子
Not deaf.

452
00:46:19,030 --> 00:46:21,530
我不是聋子，你明白了吗？
Not deaf. You understand that?

453
00:46:21,530 --> 00:46:23,520
你明白了吗？
You understand?

454
00:46:26,030 --> 00:46:29,030
啊，新鲜的空气！
Ahh, fresh air!

455
00:46:29,030 --> 00:46:31,520
让我离开这个虚伪的行列吧！
Let me out of this gilded parade.

456
00:46:32,020 --> 00:46:36,030
出去！滚出去！滚得好！
Get out! Get out of here! Good riddance!

457
00:46:40,030 --> 00:46:43,520
喔，帕罗斯，我还要吃这种东西多久？
Oh, Pavlos, how much longer do I have to eat like this?

458
00:47:07,610 --> 00:47:10,100
嘿，注意听
Hey, listen.

459
00:47:10,110 --> 00:47:14,110
她们准时走了
There they go, right on schedule.

460
00:47:14,110 --> 00:47:16,610
那些老师，记得吗？
The teachers. Remember?

461
00:47:17,610 --> 00:47:21,600
你能听到吗？她们正要离开
Can you hear them? They're going away.

462
00:47:25,610 --> 00:47:27,610
你听得到吗？
You hear them?

463
00:47:29,600 --> 00:47:31,600
是的
Yes.

464
00:47:36,280 --> 00:47:38,270
我…
I...

465
00:47:48,280 --> 00:47:51,770
我…我不认为她们会想念学校
I...I don't think they'll even miss school.

466
00:47:51,770 --> 00:47:54,770
什么？你说什么？
What? What did you say?

467
00:47:54,770 --> 00:47:57,280
醒醒
Wake up.

468
00:47:57,280 --> 00:48:01,770
我说，对我来说，她们似乎没有出去
I said, it doesn't seem to me that they're going out.

469
00:48:03,270 --> 00:48:05,780
前门在左边
A front door is on the left.

470
00:48:07,280 --> 00:48:10,770
她们的脚步声往右边走，在学校里的某处
Their footsteps are going to the right, somewhere inside the school.

471
00:48:12,270 --> 00:48:15,270
天啊，苏西
Jesus, Suzy.

472
00:48:15,270 --> 00:48:16,280
- 你真是天才  - 嗯…
- You're a genius.  - Mmm.

473
00:48:17,770 --> 00:48:19,770
好极了
Fantastic.

474
00:48:19,770 --> 00:48:23,190
为什么我以前从未注意到呢？
How come I never noticed that before?

475
00:48:23,190 --> 00:48:28,180
苏西，如果她们没有离开，她们会去哪里呢？
Suzy. If they don't leave, Where do they go?

476
00:48:28,680 --> 00:48:30,690
醒醒，苏西
Wake up. Suzy.

477
00:48:30,690 --> 00:48:35,530
快醒醒，苏西！
Come on. Wake up. Suzy!

478
00:48:37,020 --> 00:48:39,520
我好想睡觉
I'm so sleepy.

479
00:48:39,520 --> 00:48:41,520
我不知道为什么，对不起
I don't know why. I'm sorry.

480
00:48:41,520 --> 00:48:44,520
也许…
Maybe...

481
00:48:44,520 --> 00:48:47,020
也许我们能找到她们真正去的地方
Maybe we can find out where they really go.

482
00:48:48,520 --> 00:48:53,020
当然！对了
Of course! Yes.

483
00:48:56,520 --> 00:48:59,520
开始数她们走的脚步声
Begin to count the steps as they go.

484
00:49:16,350 --> 00:49:18,770
这就像寻找线索一样
It's like the search of alietne.

485
00:52:44,850 --> 00:52:46,920
放轻松
Easy.

486
00:52:48,430 --> 00:52:50,430
怎么了？
What is it? Huh?

487
00:52:50,430 --> 00:52:52,430
走吧
Come on.

488
00:52:53,930 --> 00:52:55,920
快点，我们走吧
Come on; let's go home.

489
00:53:18,680 --> 00:53:21,180
是谁？谁在那里？
Who is that? Who's there?

490
00:53:22,680 --> 00:53:24,840
放轻松，孩子
Easy, boy.

491
00:53:30,340 --> 00:53:32,350
怎么了？
What is it?

492
00:53:34,840 --> 00:53:36,920
发生了什么事？
What's happening?

493
00:53:41,590 --> 00:53:44,050
谁在那里？
Who's there?

494
00:53:48,510 --> 00:53:51,010
谁在那里？
Who's there?

495
00:54:05,170 --> 00:54:07,170
等等！
Wait!

496
00:56:03,340 --> 00:56:06,420
可怜的丹尼尔，被撕成了碎片，真令人不敢相信
Poor Daniel. Torn to pieces. Incredible.

497
00:56:06,420 --> 00:56:09,420
没错，但你不能太信任狼犬
Oh, yeah, but you can never put too much trust in wolfhounds.

498
00:56:09,420 --> 00:56:12,920
它们很疯狂，我们以前在格施塔德的别墅养过两只
They're crazy. We had two of them once at the villa in Gestaad.

499
00:56:12,920 --> 00:56:15,920
我的天啊，最先是佩特被疯子杀了
My god. First Pat gets murdered by a madman,

500
00:56:15,920 --> 00:56:18,420
而现在丹尼尔又被他的狗咬死了
And now Daniel is killed by his dog.

501
00:56:18,420 --> 00:56:20,920
对啊，也许这地方有不祥的东西
Yeah. Maybe there's a hex on the place.

502
00:56:21,420 --> 00:56:25,420
对，那我们请神父来驱魔好了
Yeah. Let's call in the exorcist and have it purged.

503
00:56:25,920 --> 00:56:29,920
- 怎么了？有什么问题吗？ - 没有，一切都很好
- What is it? Is something wrong?  - No, everything's all right.

504
00:56:30,170 --> 00:56:32,670
是私人的问题吗，亲爱的？
Is it something personal, dear?

505
00:56:32,670 --> 00:56:35,170
不是，不是那样
No, no, it's nothing like that.

506
00:56:36,670 --> 00:56:39,170
坦娜小姐，你介意吗？
Miss Tanner, would you mind?

507
00:56:39,330 --> 00:56:41,330
我想独自和苏西谈几分钟
I'd like a few minutes alone with Suzy.

508
00:56:46,840 --> 00:56:48,830
怎么回事？
Well? What is it?

509
00:56:49,330 --> 00:56:52,840
我只是想跟你谈谈最近发生的一些事情
I just wanted to talk to you about some of the things that have been happening lately.

510
00:56:53,340 --> 00:56:56,330
喔，我知道你对丹尼尔的死感到不安，我们大家都是
Oh, I know you're upset by Daniel's death, as we all have been.

511
00:56:56,340 --> 00:56:58,330
不，不只是那样
No, but it's more than that.

512
00:56:58,830 --> 00:57:01,330
有人知道谁杀了佩特吗？
Does anybody know anything about who killed Pat?

513
00:57:01,840 --> 00:57:03,340
我今天早上跟警察局长谈过话
I spoke with the chief of police just this morning.

514
00:57:03,840 --> 00:57:05,830
他告诉我，他们有一些明确的线索
He told me they had some definite clues.

515
00:57:06,330 --> 00:57:09,330
- 你知道我来的那晚有看到她  - 是的，你告诉过我
- You know that I saw her the night I arrived here.  - Yes, you told me that.

516
00:57:09,330 --> 00:57:12,790
那时她含糊地说一些奇怪无关的话
And that she was mumbling some strange, unrelated words.

517
00:57:13,340 --> 00:57:15,790
你没有告诉过我
No, you didn't tell me that.

518
00:57:15,790 --> 00:57:19,330
因为这没办法合理解释，那是在暴风雨中
Because it was something that didn't make any sense. It was in a thunderstorm.

519
00:57:19,330 --> 00:57:22,340
我没有注意去听清楚
I just didn't pay much attention to it.

520
00:57:22,340 --> 00:57:25,330
我只能清楚地听到两个字…
I only caught two words distinctly:

521
00:57:25,340 --> 00:57:27,790
“秘密”和“鸢尾花”
"Secret" and "Irises."

522
00:57:27,790 --> 00:57:31,330
我不知道这些是什么意思，但我认为也许很重要
I don't know what they mean, but I thought they might be important.

523
00:57:31,330 --> 00:57:33,340
你做得很好
You've done very well. Congratulations.

524
00:57:33,340 --> 00:57:36,330
我也不知道“秘密”或“鸢尾花”是什么意思
I don't know what the words "Secret" or "Irises" mean either.

525
00:57:36,330 --> 00:57:38,790
但我想应该要让警察知道这件事
But I think it's only right we should let the police know about it.

526
00:57:38,790 --> 00:57:43,300
我只是很惊讶你等了两天才说“哈罗”？
I'm only amazed you waited two days before... hello?

527
00:57:43,500 --> 00:57:47,080
- 你真的把事情弄糟了  - 你在说什么？
- You really messed things up.  - What are you talking about?

528
00:57:47,080 --> 00:57:50,080
因为…也许佩特在跟那天晚上
Because... Maybe Pat was talking to...

529
00:57:50,580 --> 00:57:53,090
这栋房子里的某个人说话
Someone just inside the building that night.

530
00:57:57,080 --> 00:57:59,580
我们知道那个人不是我们学校的老师
And we know that someone wasn't one of the teachers.

531
00:58:06,330 --> 00:58:08,330
来吧
Come on.

532
00:58:10,830 --> 00:58:13,330
现在你使某人落到他们调查范围内了
Now you've put them on the hunt for somebody.

533
00:58:13,340 --> 00:58:16,330
这对你来说有什么差别？
What difference does that make to you?

534
00:58:16,330 --> 00:58:18,330
很大的差别
Big difference.

535
00:58:19,330 --> 00:58:22,330
因为我是佩特的朋友
Because I was Pat's friend.

536
00:58:22,840 --> 00:58:25,330
你突然来到的时候，她正告诉我一些事情
She was telling me something When you suddenly showed up.

537
00:58:25,330 --> 00:58:28,830
她被吓坏了，然后跑了
She got scared and she ran away.

538
00:58:28,830 --> 00:58:31,330
那时她几乎陷入歇斯底里
She was in hysterics almost.

539
00:58:31,840 --> 00:58:33,830
然后她就被杀死了
And then she was killed.

540
00:58:33,830 --> 00:58:37,330
记得当你按门铃时的那个声音吗？
Remember that voice when you rang the bell?

541
00:58:37,330 --> 00:58:39,830
跟你说话的就是我
Well, that was me.

542
00:59:35,830 --> 00:59:39,820
我听到一些奇怪、难以置信和荒谬的事情
I heard strange, incredible, absurd things.

543
00:59:39,830 --> 00:59:42,330
佩特写在笔记上好几个月了
Pat was taking notes on them for months.

544
00:59:42,330 --> 00:59:45,830
在她走之前，她把笔记都给了我
And before going away, she gave me all the notes.

545
00:59:45,830 --> 00:59:49,320
我只有跟一个我非常要好的朋友说过
I've only told one person, a very good friend of mine.

546
00:59:49,330 --> 00:59:52,330
法兰克曼德尔，他是来这里参加一个会议
Frank Mandel. He's here for a convention.

547
00:59:52,830 --> 00:59:55,830
今晚我会让你读这些笔记
I'll let you read them tonight.

548
01:00:06,500 --> 01:00:10,490
苏西，醒醒，拜托，醒醒
Suzy, wake up. Please. Wake up.

549
01:00:10,490 --> 01:00:13,950
笔记不见了！有人从我那里偷走了！
The notes are gone! Someone stole them from me!

550
01:00:14,330 --> 01:00:17,750
你明白吗？笔记不见了
You understand? They disappeared.

551
01:00:17,750 --> 01:00:22,580
不要睡着！请帮帮我！
Don't fall asleep! Please help me!

552
01:00:22,830 --> 01:00:25,830
- 醒醒！帮帮我！ - 我不能
- Wake up! Help me!  - I can't.

553
01:00:26,080 --> 01:00:27,580
不能？
Can't?

554
01:00:30,070 --> 01:00:35,080
这是我唯一剩下的东西，因为我放在身边，看
This is the only thing I got left, and that's because I kept it on me. Look.

555
01:00:35,080 --> 01:00:37,570
- 看  - 这是什么？
- Look.  - What is it?

556
01:00:37,580 --> 01:00:42,080
你到底怎么了？你不记得吗？发生什么事？
What's the matter with you? Don't you remember? What's going on?

557
01:00:42,330 --> 01:00:46,330
这是让我们知道老师每晚去哪里的关键
This is the key that'll get us wherever the teachers go every night.

558
01:00:46,330 --> 01:00:50,320
昨晚我坐在你旁边时想出来的办法
I thought it out yesterday evening while I was sitting here next to you.

559
01:00:50,320 --> 01:00:56,040
苏西，你知道女巫吗？
Suzy, do you know anything about witches?

560
01:01:01,580 --> 01:01:04,580
喔，不！拜托！
Oh, no! Please!

561
01:01:06,040 --> 01:01:09,570
不要留下我一个人！
Don't leave me alone!

562
01:01:21,530 --> 01:01:24,540
我一定要逃走！
I must get away!

563
01:03:20,740 --> 01:03:24,190
等等！
Wait!

564
01:03:44,400 --> 01:03:47,400
等等！
Wait!

565
01:04:19,770 --> 01:04:22,320
等等！等等！等等！等等！
Wait, wait, wait, wait!

566
01:09:14,890 --> 01:09:17,760
在找莎拉吗？她不见了
Looking for Sara? She's disappeared.

567
01:09:17,760 --> 01:09:20,760
但这是不可能的，我昨晚还跟她说过话
But that's impossible. I just talked to her last night.

568
01:09:20,760 --> 01:09:24,770
她今天早上离开了，事实上，没有告诉任何人
She left this morning, as a matter of fact, without telling anyone.

569
01:09:24,770 --> 01:09:28,260
只是拿起她的行李就走了，她被听到在大约六点钟时离开
Just packed her bags and left. She was heard leaving about 6:00.

570
01:09:28,260 --> 01:09:31,760
- 你有听到她离开，不是吗？ - 莎拉？喔，是的
- You heard her leave, didn't you?  - Sara? Oh, yes.

571
01:09:31,760 --> 01:09:35,270
我听到大门被关上和她的脚步声离开了大厅
I heard the door close and her footsteps going down the hall.

572
01:09:35,270 --> 01:09:39,260
然后我听到汽车驶离街道的声音，我猜有人在等她吧
And then I heard a car driving off down the street. I guess someone was waiting for her.

573
01:09:39,260 --> 01:09:44,270
- 但这是不可能的  - 如果她不高兴在这里，她可以告诉别人
- But it's impossible.  - If she wasn't happy here, she could've told someone.

574
01:09:44,770 --> 01:09:47,260
为什么要像小偷一样偷偷溜走？
Why sneak off like a thief?

575
01:09:57,510 --> 01:10:01,510
你好，我可以跟法兰克曼德尔说话吗？好的，谢谢你
Hello. May I speak to Frank Mandel, please? Yes, thank you.

576
01:10:03,020 --> 01:10:06,010
你好，我是苏西邦妮
Hello. This is Suzy Bannion.

577
01:10:06,010 --> 01:10:09,010
不，我们没有见过面，我是莎拉的朋友
No, we've never met. I'm a friend of Sara's.

578
01:10:09,010 --> 01:10:13,520
是的，你好，你知道莎拉在哪里吗？
Yes. Hello. Do you happen to know where Sara is?

579
01:10:15,010 --> 01:10:18,010
她今天早上从学校失踪了
Well, she disappeared from school this morning.

580
01:10:18,510 --> 01:10:21,510
是的，似乎她带着所有行李离开了
Yes, it seems she left and took all her luggage.

581
01:10:21,510 --> 01:10:26,010
是的，嗯，听着，我今天可以跟你见个面吗？
Yes. Uh, listen, could I see you sometime today?

582
01:10:27,010 --> 01:10:30,010
嗯，我真的很担心她
Well, I'm really worried about her.

583
01:10:30,010 --> 01:10:34,510
喔，好极了，在哪里呢？
Oh, great. Where?

584
01:10:34,510 --> 01:10:38,010
在会议中心，好的，我会去那里见你
At the convention center. Okay. I'll see you there.

585
01:10:38,010 --> 01:10:41,510
她没有告知任何同学，我已经问过所有人
She didn't inform any of her classmates. I've already asked all of them.

586
01:10:41,510 --> 01:10:45,010
真烦人，我不明白她为什么要这样做
It's very upsetting. I can't understand why she did it.

587
01:10:45,510 --> 01:10:48,010
我是受他们家庭请托的监护人
I'm the one who's held responsible by their families.

588
01:10:48,010 --> 01:10:51,640
我会打电话给她在日内瓦的父亲，或许她已经到那里了
I'll call her father in Geneva. Perhaps she might have gone there.

589
01:11:04,630 --> 01:11:08,640
我已经打电话给莎拉的父亲，他是意大利驻日内瓦的领事
I've already phoned Sara's father. He's the Italian consul in Geneva.

590
01:11:08,640 --> 01:11:13,130
但他今天不在那里，去度周末了
But he wasn't there today. He was away for the weekend.

591
01:11:13,130 --> 01:11:17,130
他们说他星期一会回来，而且他们不知道关于她的任何事情
They said he'd be back by monday, and they don't know anything about her there.

592
01:11:17,130 --> 01:11:20,140
你知道我为什么这么担心吗？
Well, do you understand Why I'm so worried?

593
01:11:20,140 --> 01:11:24,630
我知道，但我们也只能等她父亲回来了
Yes, but before we both get upset, let's wait for the father's return.

594
01:11:24,630 --> 01:11:28,140
也许他们今天早上会合一起离开的
Maybe they got together this morning and went off on their own.

595
01:11:28,140 --> 01:11:34,130
我非常了解她，她是我三年前的病人
I know her quite well. She was a patient of mine three years ago.

596
01:11:34,130 --> 01:11:38,140
- 你知道了吗？ - 我甚至不知道你是精神科医师
- Were you aware of that?  - No. I didn't even know you were a psychiatrist.

597
01:11:38,140 --> 01:11:42,630
她曾经在她母亲过世时精神崩溃过
Well, she had a nervous breakdown after her mother's death,

598
01:11:43,130 --> 01:11:45,130
所以她来接受我的治疗
And she came to me for treatment.

599
01:11:45,630 --> 01:11:49,140
在她病情好转之后，我们仍然是朋友
After she got better again, we remained friends,

600
01:11:49,140 --> 01:11:54,130
但最近她因为一个朋友向她灌输一些思想而感到不安
But lately she was upset about some notions put into her head by a friend of hers.

601
01:11:54,130 --> 01:11:57,130
- 我希望那个人不是你？ - 不是
- Not you, I hope?  - No.

602
01:11:57,390 --> 01:11:59,880
那是一些疯狂的想法
They were kind of wild ideas.

603
01:11:59,890 --> 01:12:04,380
她发现塔姆学院是于…
She had discovered that the Tam academy was founded...

604
01:12:04,510 --> 01:12:09,010
一八九五年由一位希腊移民海莲娜玛蔻斯建立的
In 1895 by a certain Helena Markos, A Greek immigrant,

605
01:12:09,010 --> 01:12:12,510
而当地人认为她是一个女巫
And that the local people believed her to be a witch.

606
01:12:14,010 --> 01:12:18,010
- 我猜你知道这件事了？ - 不，但我有一种奇怪的感觉…
- I guess you knew that?  - No. But I have a strange feeling...

607
01:12:18,010 --> 01:12:23,510
好像有人已经跟我说过这件事，或是类似的事
That somebody already told me about it...Or something similar.

608
01:12:23,510 --> 01:12:25,510
我不记得了
I can't...can't remember.

609
01:12:25,510 --> 01:12:29,500
那真的让莎拉发挥想像力在十九世纪初期…
Well, that really got Sara's imagination going. Earlier in the 19th century,

610
01:12:29,880 --> 01:12:34,380
玛蔻斯女士被数个欧洲国家驱逐出境
The Markos woman had been expelled from several european countries.

611
01:12:34,380 --> 01:12:39,880
她似乎做过一些事，才使得教徒迫害她
She seemed to have something about her which urged religious people to persecute her.

612
01:12:40,380 --> 01:12:44,880
她也写过一些书，我读过其中一本
She also wrote a number of books, and I read that among the initiated,

613
01:12:45,380 --> 01:12:48,500
书名叫做“黑暗女王”
She went by the name "The Black Queen."

614
01:12:48,500 --> 01:12:52,510
在她定居于这里之后，她变成很多街头流言的主角
After she settled down here, she became the subject of a lot of gossip.

615
01:12:52,510 --> 01:12:56,510
虽然如此，她还是设法得到一大笔钱
Nevertheless, she managed to put her hands on a great deal of money,

616
01:12:56,510 --> 01:12:59,000
然后她建立了塔姆学院
And she founded the Tam academy...

617
01:12:59,000 --> 01:13:04,130
起先是教导舞蹈和神秘学的学校
At first a sort of school of dance and occult sciences.

618
01:13:04,130 --> 01:13:07,120
但是没有维持很久，因为在一九〇五年
But that didn't last long, because in 1905,

619
01:13:07,130 --> 01:13:10,130
在她年满一百岁、也是被诅咒的第十年
After being hounded and cursed at for ten years,

620
01:13:10,130 --> 01:13:13,630
玛蔻斯夫人死于一场大火
Madame Markos died in a fire.

621
01:13:13,630 --> 01:13:17,120
那个事件和巫术一样被人们所关注
That's all there is, as far as witchcraft is concerned.

622
01:13:17,120 --> 01:13:22,260
于是学校被她最喜爱的学生接管，神秘学的课程也被完全废除
The school was taken over by her favorite pupil. The study of the occult was abandoned.

623
01:13:22,260 --> 01:13:26,750
不久后这个地方变成一所着名的舞蹈学院
And soon the place became the famous dance academy.

624
01:13:26,750 --> 01:13:31,750
但这跟当一个女巫有什么关系？
But what does it mean to be a witch?

625
01:13:32,000 --> 01:13:35,380
从一个唯物论者和精神科医师的角度来说
Well, as a believer in the material world and a psychiatrist to boot,

626
01:13:35,380 --> 01:13:39,880
我相信现今对魔法和神秘学的信仰的传播…
I'm convinced that the current spread of belief in magic and the occult...

627
01:13:39,880 --> 01:13:43,380
是精神病的一部分
Is part of mental illness.

628
01:13:43,380 --> 01:13:48,880
坏运气不是摔破一面镜子带来的，而是由坏心情带来的
Bad luck isn't brought by broken mirrors, but by broken minds.

629
01:13:50,380 --> 01:13:52,840
抱歉，米辽斯
Excuse me. Milius?

630
01:13:52,920 --> 01:13:55,410
米辽斯教授可以比我更清楚回答你的问题
Professor Milius can answer your question better than I can.

631
01:13:55,920 --> 01:13:58,920
他写过一本叫做“妄想狂或魔法”的书，相信我
He wrote a book called paranoia or magic, and believe me,

632
01:13:58,920 --> 01:14:00,920
那是这个领域的权威着作
It's the final word on the subject.

633
01:14:01,420 --> 01:14:05,420
不好意思，米辽斯，假如你不介意，我想介绍一位我的朋友
Excuse me, Milius. If you don't mind, I'd like you to meet a friend of mine.

634
01:14:05,420 --> 01:14:09,420
- 小姐  - 她对你最喜欢的话题很感兴趣…
- Fraulein.  - She's interested in your favorite subject:

635
01:14:09,420 --> 01:14:11,920
女巫
Witches.

636
01:14:11,920 --> 01:14:15,420
你能跟她说一些神秘事物的事情吗？
Can you tell her something about the mysterious?

637
01:14:16,920 --> 01:14:19,920
那么，我要走了，我有一个约会
Well, I have to go. I have an appointment to keep.

638
01:14:19,920 --> 01:14:22,420
保持联络
Keep me posted, Hmm?

639
01:14:22,420 --> 01:14:24,910
你好，我很抱歉打扰你
Hello. I'm sorry to bother you.

640
01:14:24,910 --> 01:14:29,420
啊，那你想要知道些什么呢？
Ah, so, what would you like to know?

641
01:14:29,420 --> 01:14:32,920
- 你相信有女巫的存在吗？ - 啊
- Do you believe in the existence of witches?  - Ah.

642
01:14:32,920 --> 01:14:36,920
我知道有些女人被称为女巫
I have known some women who are said to be witches.

643
01:14:36,920 --> 01:14:40,420
- 真的吗？ - 我已经研究这个现象很久了
- Really?  - I have studied the phenomenon for a long time.

644
01:14:40,420 --> 01:14:42,920
我的观点是那是同时期精神病学的
I am of the opinion that it is an important appendage...

645
01:14:43,410 --> 01:14:46,420
重要附属物
Of contemporary psychiatry.

646
01:14:46,420 --> 01:14:48,420
你不相信吗，亲爱的？
You're skeptical, my dear.

647
01:14:48,420 --> 01:14:51,920
坦白说，这有点让人难以相信
Well, frankly, it is a little hard to believe.

648
01:14:53,910 --> 01:14:59,040
- 女巫是什么样的人？ - 她们是邪恶、消极和有毁灭性的
- What do witches do?  - They are malefic, negative and destructive.

649
01:14:59,040 --> 01:15:03,540
她们对于神秘学的知识让她们得到极大的能力
Their knowledge of the art of the occult gives them tremendous powers.

650
01:15:04,040 --> 01:15:09,040
她们能改变事物的发展和人的生命，但只会造成危害
They can change the course of events and people's lives, but only to do harm.

651
01:15:10,040 --> 01:15:13,540
- 你不相信我吗？ - 不，我…
- You don't believe me?  - No, I...

652
01:15:13,540 --> 01:15:17,040
她们的目标是累积个人财富
Their goal is to accumulate great personal wealth,

653
01:15:17,040 --> 01:15:21,040
但只能藉由伤害别人来达到
But that can only be achieved by injury to others.

654
01:15:21,050 --> 01:15:24,540
她们能引起痛苦、疾病，甚至是死亡…
They can cause suffering, sickness and even the death...

655
01:15:24,540 --> 01:15:28,540
不管谁，不管任何理由，只要触怒她们
Of those who, for whatever reason, have offended them.

656
01:15:30,800 --> 01:15:34,040
为什么你对神秘学有兴趣呢？
Why do you have all this interest in the occult?

657
01:15:34,040 --> 01:15:37,040
因为有一些朋友跟我谈到女巫
Because some friends spoke to me about witches.

658
01:15:37,040 --> 01:15:40,040
我也看过一些文献资料
I read some stuff.

659
01:15:40,040 --> 01:15:43,040
你听说过“海莲娜玛蔻斯”吗？
Have you ever heard of Helena Markos?

660
01:15:43,540 --> 01:15:46,540
喔，是的，她是一位非常着名的黑暗女王
Oh, yes. She was a very famous black queen.

661
01:15:46,540 --> 01:15:49,540
一位拥有极大邪恶力量的天才女巫
A powerful witch with a tremendous talent for doing evil,

662
01:15:49,540 --> 01:15:51,540
一位真正的魔法夫人
A real mistress of magic.

663
01:15:51,910 --> 01:15:54,910
她居住并死在这个城市，你知道吗？
She lived and died in the city. Did you know that?

664
01:15:55,420 --> 01:15:59,920
知道，那么这里可能有女巫公会吗？
Yes. And might there exist a guild of witches?

665
01:15:59,920 --> 01:16:02,910
正确的说法应该是女巫集会
The correct term would be a coven of witches.

666
01:16:02,910 --> 01:16:05,920
一个女人成为女王，她的魔力就比…
A woman becomes queen of her magic is a hundred times more powerful...

667
01:16:06,420 --> 01:16:08,920
集会里其他人强一百倍，就好像一条蛇
Than the rest of the coven, which is like a serpent.

668
01:16:08,920 --> 01:16:12,910
它的力量取决于领导者，也就是取决于它的头
Its strength rests with its leader... That is, with its head.

669
01:16:12,910 --> 01:16:16,920
一个失去领导者的集会就好像一条无头的眼镜蛇…
A coven deprived of its leader is like a headless cobra:

670
01:16:16,920 --> 01:16:19,410
是无害的
Harmless.

671
01:16:19,910 --> 01:16:23,410
现今的人类怀疑自然的精神力
Skepticism is the natural reaction of people nowadays,

672
01:16:23,410 --> 01:16:26,420
但魔法至今是存在的
But magic is ever present.

673
01:16:26,920 --> 01:16:30,290
换句话说
In other words:

674
01:16:35,290 --> 01:16:37,790
魔法无处不在
Which means that magic is everywhere,

675
01:16:38,290 --> 01:16:41,290
而且遍及全世界，这是个被确认的事实
And all over the world, it's a recognized fact.

676
01:16:41,290 --> 01:16:44,460
一直都是
Always.

677
01:16:58,410 --> 01:17:01,410
玛克？玛克？
Mark? Mark?

678
01:17:09,910 --> 01:17:13,410
抱歉，大家去哪里了？
Excuse me. Where is everybody?

679
01:17:13,410 --> 01:17:17,910
她们全都去剧院看波修瓦芭蕾的首演了
They have all gone to the theater for the opening of the Bolshoi.

680
01:17:17,910 --> 01:17:20,910
- 为什么没有人告诉我这件事？ - 我不知道
- Then why didn't anyone tell me about it?  - I don't know.

681
01:17:21,410 --> 01:17:24,910
坦娜小姐把票发给每个学生
Miss Tanner obtained tickets for everyone.

682
